creator: ALG Software Lab
descriptionHtml:
This application is a comprehensive guide to digital and analog sensors compatible with Arduino. It provides detailed descriptions, usage instructions, integration steps, and practical code examples to help users seamlessly incorporate sensors into their projects. Whether you're working on home automation, robotics, IoT applications, or DIY electronics, this app simplifies the process of understanding and implementing various sensors and modules.

The app provides clear circuit diagrams, connection instructions, and setup guides for each sensor. Includes ready-to-use Arduino sketches with explanations for easy implementation and support with Arduino Uno, Nano and Mega boards. It Designed for beginners and advanced users, making sensor integration effortless.

A wide range of digital and analog sensors and modules is covered:

• Distance measurement
• Temperature and humidity sensors
• Pressure and temperature sensors
• Light sensors
• Vibration sensors
• Movement sensors
• Infrared modules
• Magnetic field sensors
• Touch sensors
• Gas sensors
• Soil moisture and water sensors
• LED modules
• LED matrices
• Buttons and joysticks
• Sound modules
• Motors and relays
• Accelerometers and gyroscopes
• Motion detection sensors
• Real-time clock modules

The content is available in the following languages: English, French, German, Indonesian, Italian, Polish, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish, Turkish, and Ukrainian.

Note: The Arduino trademark, as well as all other trade names mentioned in this program, are registered trademarks of their respective companies. This program is developed by an independent developer and is in no way affiliated with these companies and is not an official Arduino training course.
